{{Infobox figure skater |name= Nancy Ludington |image= |caption= |fullname= Nancy Irene Rouillard |altname= Nancy Irene Ludington |country= [[United States]] |formercountry= |birth_date= {{birth date and age|1939|7|25}} |birth_place= [[Stoneham, Massachusetts]] |hometown= |residence= |death_date= |death_place= |height= |partner= |formerpartner= [[Ronald Ludington]] |coach= |formercoach= |choreographer= |formerchoreographer= |skating club= Commonwealth Figure Skating Club |retired= 1960 |medaltemplates= <!-- see [[Template:MedalRelatedTemplates]] --> {{MedalCountry| [[United States]]}} {{MedalSport | Pairs' [[Figure skating]]}} {{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}} {{MedalBronze | [[1960 Winter Olympics|1960 Squaw Valley]] | [[Figure skating at the 1960 Winter Olympics|Pairs]]}} {{MedalCompetition|[[World Figure Skating Championships|World Championships]]}} {{MedalBronze| [[1959 World Figure Skating Championships|1959 Colorado Springs]]|Pairs}} {{MedalCompetition|[[North American Figure Skating Championships|North American Championships]]}} {{MedalBronze| [[1957 North American Figure Skating Championships|1957 Rochester]]|Pairs}} }} {{MedalTop}} {{MedalSport | [[Figure skating]]}} {{MedalCountry|[[United States]]}} {{MedalBronze | [[1960 Winter Olympics|1960 Squaw Valley]] | [[Figure skating at the 1960 Winter Olympics|Pairs]]}} {{MedalBottom}} '''Nancy Irene Rouillard''' ([[married name]]s: Ludington, Graham, born July 25, 1939) is an [[United States|American]] [[pair skater]].
==Personal life== She was born in [[Stoneham, Massachusetts]]. She has been married twice, once to pairs partner [[Ronald Ludington]] in 1957 and the second time to Frank Graham.
==Career== She began competing with [[Ronald Ludington]] in 1956 and she won her first national title under her maiden name. She changed her name professionally after she married Ludington in 1957. The Ludingtons went on to win the bronze medal at the [[1960 Winter Olympics]]. They also won the [[U.S. Figure Skating Championships|U.S. national title]] between 1957 and 1960, after having been the junior national champions in 1956. They are also the 1959 [[World Figure Skating Championships|World bronze medalists]].
